         <h2 class="title">Attractions</h2>

         <p>Despite Louisville&rsquo;s size, a great many points of interest are located within ten minutes (2-5 miles) of the hotel.</p>

         <p>Further, unlike some other metropolitan regions with populations exceeding a million, Louisville can typically be navigated quickly from end to end.</p>

         <p>Whether you&rsquo;ll be visiting an art museum, wandering any of our myriad award-winning parks, doing some antiquing, touring a distillery (bourbon or brandy&ndash;pick your poison), snuggling inside a cat caf&eacute;, eating until you&rsquo;ve reached maximum capacity, seeking out historical facts behind our local ghosts, spending quality time with the skeletons of a couple of Catholic saints, or even, say, zip-lining inside a giant cavern, it&rsquo;s all within easy reach.</p>

         <p>There&rsquo;ll be plenty of structured activities organized by the Convergence committee and others during the three official days, but there&rsquo;s really quite a lot to do here, so you might want to consider extending your stay.</p>

